EXTENDED OUTLOOK
THURSDAY TO SUNDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 132300 UTC
ON THURSDAY EVENING A BROAD AREA OF LOW PRESSURE IS CENTRED IN THE BALTIC
SEA WITH AN AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE CENTRED IN THE EERN ATLANTIC JUST TO
THE SW OF ICELAND. A RESULTING N FLOW LIES ACROSS THE N SEA. ON FRIDAY THE
AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE BUILDS SLWY EWARDS ACROSS THE UK AS THE BALTIC LOW
MOVS AWAY E ALTHOUGH THE STRG N SEA FLOW IS MAINTAINED. DURING SATURDAY
THE AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE CONTINUES TO SLWY BUILD EWARDS TO COVER MAINLAND
UK RESULTING IN THE STRG AND GENERALLY N TO NW FLOW WKN GRADUALLY EASING.
ON SUNDAY THE HIGH PRESSURE REMAINS SLOW MOV ACROSS MUCH OF THE UK AND SURROUNDING
WATERS. NO GALES ARE EXP ACROSS PORTPATRICK THROUGH THE PERIOD HOWEVER STRG
WINDS LIKELY AFFECTING SEA AREA FAIR ISLE LATE THURSDAY AND EARLY FRIDAY
BEFORE SLWY EASING INTO SATURDAY
